The paper discusses timing-based side-channel attacks and proposes a new technique called Ozone to provide total protection from such attacks. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the implementation of Ozone using a special hardware thread, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper evaluates Ozone using security-sensitive kernels, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
